<div id="aueditable"><!--DO NOT MODIFY THIS LINE AND ABOVE-->

<h1>Dreams and Dreaming</h1><div id="pubinfo"><em>First published Thu Apr 9, 2015; substantive revision Mon Jan 26, 2026</em></div>

<div id="preamble">

<p>
Dreams, dreaming, and sleep have been discussed in diverse areas of
philosophy ranging from epistemology to ethics, ontology, and more
recently philosophy of mind and philosophy of cognitive science. This
entry provides an overview of major themes in the philosophy of sleep
and dreaming with a focus on Western philosophy and relevant
scientific findings.</p>
</div> 

<div id="toc">
<!--Entry Contents-->
<ul>
